<H3> <TI>   Chen Muhua To Receive UNICEF Award for China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chen Muhua To Receive UNICEF Award for China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3004043094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0324 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3004043094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New York, April 29 (XINHUA) -- Chen Muhua, 
vice-chairman of China's National People's Congress, arrived 
here today to receive a reward by the United Nation's Children's 
Fund (UNICEF). 
  UNICEF will present its Maurice Pate Award, which includes a 
25,000 U.S. dollars stipend, on May 2, to the All-China Women's 
Federation, whose president now is Chen Muhua. 
  The All-China Women's Federation is selected for its 
exemplary leadership in promoting the well-being of children and 
women on a nationwide scale. 
  The award, named in honour of the first UNICEF executive 
director, is given annually for extraodinary and exemplary 
leadership in, and contribution to, advancement of the survival, 
protection and development of children. 
  It is the first time the reward has been given to China. 

</TEXT>

