<H3> <TI>   Representative to Singapore Transferred to Denmark </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Representative to Singapore Transferred to Denmark </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704112894 Taipei Voice of Free China in English 0200 GMT 
22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2704112894 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei Voice of Free China </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Text] ROC [Republic of China] representative to Singapore 
Chen Yu-chu is scheduled to depart the city state on 26 April, 
at which time he will head to Denmark to assume his new 
diplomatic posting. Meanwhile, the newly appointed ROC 
representative to Singapore, Chiu Chin-yi, will fly to Singapore 
on 29 April to take up his new position. Chen is a senior 
diplomat in the ROC foreign service. He has served in his post 
in Singapore since May 1990. Over the past four years, many 
changes have transpired in relations between the ROC on Taiwan 
and Singapore. The most important change has been that 
Singapore established formal diplomatic relations with Communist 
China in August 1990. During his tenure, Chen has worked to 
maintain substantive ties between the two countries, exhibited 
in the increase in private exchanges between the two sides and 
strengthened trade relations. Government officials from both 
countries often commonly made calls to the other. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

